.TH BUNPY-HELP 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-help \- print long-form help for a subcommand
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy help
[\fIcommand\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
With no argument, prints the top-level usage (same as
.BR "bunpy --help" ).
With a subcommand name, prints the long-form help for that
subcommand. The output is identical to
.BI "bunpy " command " --help" \fR.
.PP
If
.I command
is not a known subcommand,
.B bunpy help
exits non-zero with a hint to run
.B bunpy help
without arguments to see the list.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy (1).
